Lincoln Road Race
description: Lincoln Road Race p/b Phat Tire Bike Shop
course: The road race takes place on the course that has been used as the Arkansas State Championship road race course for 2008 & 2009. The course is flat to rolling with two climbs.
directions: From HWY 62 in Lincoln turn north on West Hwy. Go approx half a mile and turn right on Holt Rd. Look for parking on the right in about a block.

title: Lake Sylvia Slobberknocker Mtb Challenge
description: The event consists of two races. There is a one-lap, 33 mile race and a two-lap, 66 mile race. The two-lap race is part of the Arkansas Mountain Bike Marathon series.
course: The course is a 32.6 mile loop with approximately 3,400 feet of climbing on gravel forest service roads in the Flatside Wilderness area of the Ouachita National Forest.
registration: On-line registration on BikeReg.com. A late fee of $10 appies after on-line registration closes. Race packet pick-up and late regiistration begins Friday, April 29 at the Chainwheel Bike Shop at 10300 N. Rodney Parham Rd. in Littlew Rock, Arkansas and Saturday morning before the race at the Camp Ouachita staging area from 6:30 to 7:30 am.
notes: Race results posted at approximately 2:30 after 15 minute protest period. Lunch served from 12;30 TO 3:30 pm. One free meal ticket for all registered riders. Additional tickets on-site for $5.00 each. Pay-outs to top three finishers (Men, Women and Single-speed) of 66 mile race. Medals or trophies to top three finishers of 33 mile race.
directions: From Little Rock, Arkansas: At I- 430 take Highway 10 (Cantrell Rd.) west. Drive approximately 25 miles and turn left on AR 324 W. Drive approximately 3.6 miles to staging area at Camp Ouachita.

title: Revenge of the Ridge
description: Revenge of the Ridge is a cross country mountain bike race in Mena Ar.  It is apart of the AMBCS.
course: The course is 9 miles for Cat 3 (2 4.5 mile loops).  14 miles for Cat 2 (2 7 mile loops) and 21 for Cat 1 (3 7 mile loops).
registration: Saturday May 21 registration from 5 pm to 7 pm at Jansen Park.  Sunday May 22 registration from 7:30 pm to 30 min prior to cat start.

title: The Central Arkansas Star-spangled Classic Criteri
description: The Central Arkansas Star-spangled Classic Criterium
course: Course Description: A flat, closed, 1.0 mile course with one 180o, one left, and three right turns located on Riverfront Drive in North Little Rock, Arkansas.
registration: Registration: On-line at BikeReg.com and on-site starting at 7:00 a.m. the day of the event at River Trail Station located in Riverfront Park behind the floodwall.  Entry fee is $35.00 for the first race and $20 for an additional race.  Non-licensed USAC riders (cat 5 only) must purchase a $10 one-day USAC license.
notes:
General Rules: All 2011 USA Cycling rules are in effect.  Valid and current USAC license must be presented at registration.  Promoter reserves the right to adjust start times, cancel/combine events and modify prize lists as necessary.

Events will be held rain or shine.  Helmets must be worn on the bike at all times.  All numbers supplied by the promoter must be used.  No folding or cutting of numbers is allowed.  See example at registration for specific placement.  Junior riders must use gearing as per USA Cycling regulations.  A wheel pit will be in place (wheels in - wheels out).

Visit www.team-carve.com to view a map of the race course.
directions: Directions: From  I-30, take the Broadway exit (#141B) and go east on Broadway, then west on Riverfront Drive, to Riverfront Park.

Highroller's Cyclocross Adventure
description: The First Annual Highroller Cyclery Cyclocross Adventure. Season opener for the Arkansas Super-Prestige Cyclocross Points Series. Race day registration only.
course: The course will be held in a city park and will combine technical sections as well as long grassy power sections. There will most likely not be any long sustained climbs. A sand pit is currently in the race course as well.
registration:
Registration starts at seven in the morning on October 16 2011 registration closes 20 minutes before each race.
*Cash Prize not to exceed $499 per category*
notes: Race will be held unless the venue provider revokes the permit based on race day conditions. IE rain, sleet, hail, etc.
directions:
From I540 take exit 62 for Martin Luther King Blvd and head East. Drive east until you intersect Hwy 71. Continue straight through the light and take the 3rd Right Turn on Block Street. Continue on Block until you see the race. 

Walker Park 10 W 15th St.Fayetteville, AR 72701

title: Reservoir Cross
description: Cyclocross in the heart of Arkansas!  Reservoir Cross caps off a weekend of racing in Little Rock.  Great venue, with start, finish, and registration at a covered pavilion complete with fireplace, playground, food and drink available, and beginner\'s race.
course: Hilly and varied 1.5-mile circuit over dirt, grass, pavement, and gravel.
registration: Registration available online or on day of event.  $25 entry fee, $15 for juniors and beginners race.  All racers required to carry USAC license; one-day USAC licenses available on-site for $10.  Each additional race only $10.
notes: All races held under USAC cyclocross rules. Warm-up will be permitted on the course only between events at race officialâ€™s discretion. Races held rain or shine. Helmet must be worn at all times while riding a bicycle. Mountain bikes are permitted but without bar-end extensions. The promoter reserves the right to combine categories and/or prizes due to attendance.
directions: From I-430, take Cantrell Rd exit and drive east on Cantrell.  After one mile, do NOT turn on Reservoir Rd but continue straight on Cantrell.  Half a mile farther, turn right at entrance to Reservoir Park.

title: Gearhead Cyclocross
description: Join Gearhead Outfitters for a fun day of cyclocross! We will have races for all ability levels.  The course will be very spectator friendly and there is a playground and walking path next to the race area. Cyclocross is fast growing fall/winter branch of cycling that combines elements of road racing, mountain biking and steeplechase. There will usually be at least one dismount and remount of your bike on the course.
course: Located Access 3 at Craighead Forest. A 1 mile loop containing grass, pavement and sand.   There will be one stair section dismount and one barrier section.
registration: Registration will be on site only,  opening from 9:30am until 30 minutes prior to your event.  Cash or checks accepted.
notes: All races will score points in the Arkansas Superprestige Series.  See http://arkansascyclocross.blogspot.com/ for more information.
directions:
Address of park: 4910 S Culberhouse Rd, Jonesboro, AR 72404
